tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE calibration_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    project_name TEXT,
    printer_name TEXT,
    nozzle_temperature INT,
    bed_temperature INT,
    filament_material TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE printer_calibration_data (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    project_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    printer_model VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    nozzle_temperature INT NOT NULL,
    bed_temperature INT NOT NULL,
    layer_height FLOAT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE printer (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    manufacturer VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    build_volume VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    calibration_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE CalibrationData (
    calibration_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_id INT,
    project_id INT,
    calibration_date DATE,
    calibration_settings JSONB
);

CREATE TABLE Printer (
    printer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_model VARCHAR(50),
    printer_type VARCHAR(50),
    manufacturer VARCHAR(50),
    purchase_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE Project (
    project_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    project_name VARCHAR(100),
    project_description TEXT,
    project_owner VARCHAR(50),
    project_status VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE PrintJobData (
    job_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_name TEXT,
    job_start_time TIMESTAMP,
    job_end_time TIMESTAMP,
    filament_used DECIMAL,
    print_quality_rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE CalibrationData (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_id INT,
    project_id INT,
    calibration_date DATE,
    calibration_settings TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Printer (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    manufacturer VARCHAR(50),
    build_volume VARCHAR(20),
    technology VARCHAR(30)
);

CREATE TABLE PrintQuality (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_id INT,
    project_id INT,
    calibration_id INT,
    defects_count INT,
    quality_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE CalibrationSettings (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_id INT,
    nozzle_temp INT,
    bed_temp INT,
    print_speed INT
);
